This paper discusses the feasibility of using side-channel sensors for industrial intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation and employment of these sensors in an industrial environment, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of sensor data to provide enhanced insight could also involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
